text.section:
Within sixty (60) days following the close of the fiscal year, the district shall:
File with the county clerk of each county with territory in the district a certification showing any of the following information that has changed since the last filing by the district:
The name of the district;
A map or general description of its service area;
The statutory authority under which it was created; and
The names, addresses, and the date of expiration of the terms of office of the members of its governing body and chief executive officer;
Submit for review a copy of the summary financial statement with the fiscal court of each county with territory in the district; and
Publish, in lieu of the provisions of KRS 424.220, but in compliance with other applicable provisions of KRS Chapter 424, the names and addresses of the members of its governing body and chief executive officer, and either a summary financial statement, which includes the location of supporting documents, or the location of district financial records which may be examined by the public.
